properties.areaDesc: Wenatchee Area; Moses Lake Area; Waterville Plateau
properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 11 at 12:47PM PST until February 11 at 6:00PM PST by NWS Spokane WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...West winds 10 to 20 mph with gusts up to 35 mph localized
higher gusts possible near 45 mph.

* WHERE...Moses Lake Area, Wenatchee Area Leavenworth, and
Waterville Plateau.

* WHEN...Until 6 PM PST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds could blow around unsecured objects.
Tree limbs could be blown down and a few power outages may
result.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...High profile vehicles could have difficulty
driving in gusty areas.
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM PST THIS EVENING
